      <section eId="sec_44_14_162">
        <num>44-14-162</num>
        <content>
          <p>All deeds under power shall contain recitals setting forth the giving of notice in compliance with Code Section 44-14-162.2. The effect of such recitals shall be to protect the validity of the title of any subsequent purchaser in good faith other than the lender.</p>
          <p>(Ga. L. 1981, p. 834, ยง 2; Ga. L. 2012, p. 1079, ยง 2/SB 333.)</p>
          <p>The 2012 amendment,
      effective July 1, 2012, deleted "or a statement of the facts which render the same inapplicable thereto, which facts may include, without limitation, the nonresidential character of the property" at the end of the first sentence. See Editor's notes for applicability.</p>
        </content>
      </section>
